      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed following ASME V&V 20 guidelines. GCI values for hemolysis index are below 8% on the medium mesh used for production runs. Gradation 4 would require GCI below 5% with extrapolated solution reported; this threshold was not reached.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Gradation 4 requires GCI < 5% on the production mesh for all five operating points, Richardson extrapolation reported, and asymptotic range confirmed. The medium mesh achieves GCI of 6–8%, falling short of the threshold."
