      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (normalised index of hemolysis, NIH) is directly relevant to the clinical endpoint. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distributions, exposure time histograms) are reported but not formally linked to the regulatory acceptance threshold in the validation report."
