      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments use the FDA generic pump geometry under benchtop conditions with bovine blood analogue. The COU requires prediction for human blood under implanted VAD operating conditions. Geometric fidelity is high; fluid analogue and physiological operating envelope fidelity are moderate.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Gradation 4 requires that validation experiments use the same device geometry, fluid, and operating conditions as the COU, or that demonstrated equivalency arguments are provided and accepted. The use of bovine blood analogue and benchtop conditions without formal equivalency justification prevents achievement of Gradation 4."
