      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ is performed on the four most influential model inputs (power-law exponents, viscosity, inlet velocity profile). Sobol sensitivity indices are reported. One input (red blood cell fragility parameter) lacks a validated distribution and is treated as a fixed nominal value.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Gradation 4 requires that all inputs with non-negligible sensitivity indices have validated probability distributions derived from experimental data, and that the full Monte Carlo propagation is reported with convergence diagnostics. The uncharacterised RBC fragility parameter prevents Gradation 4."
