    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factors achieving levels below the required level, the regulatory submission is accepted provisionally on the basis of compensating controls: (1) Monte Carlo UQ bounds are conservative relative to the clinical hemolysis threshold, (2) a post-market surveillance plan with hemolysis monitoring is in place, and (3) the FDA generic pump geometry provides the highest available fidelity benchmark. NOTE: Several factors (Numerical code verification, Output comparison, Use error, Model form, Equivalency of input parameters) lack structured acceptanceCriteria documentation — this constitutes the W-AR-01 weakener embedded in this adversarial package.",
